# Backend Python Standards

- Follow DRY: extract shared logic into utility/service functions; avoid copy-paste blocks.
- Prefer small, single-purpose functions and clear module boundaries.
- Add type hints for function inputs and return values.
- Write docstrings for all public functions and classes.
- Public docstrings should include purpose, args, returns, and raised errors when relevant.
- Keep naming explicit and domain-oriented (`notebook_service`, `graph_state`, `summary_node`).
- Add or update tests when behavior changes.
